OL,3,CTransport Secretary resigns over
OL,4,Cmaking false police report
OL,6,FTransport Secretary Louise Haigh has
OL,7,Fresigned after admitting she pleaded
OL,8,Fguilty after she incorrectly told
OL,9,Fpolice that a work mobile phone was
OL,10,Fstolen in 2013.
OL,12,FMs Haigh admitted an offence in 2014
OL,13,Ffollowing the incident, according to
OL,14,FSky News and the Times.
OL,16,FShe had reported to police that the
OL,17,Fdevice had been stolen when she was
OL,18,F"mugged" in 2013.
